  <title>Live Region Commands</title>
  <p>
    The following commands can be used to access dynamically-updated
    content on web pages which have been made accessible through ARIA.
  </p>
  <list>
    <item>
      <p>
        Monitor live regions:
        <keyseq><key>Orca Modifier</key><key>Backslash</key></keyseq>
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Advance live region politeness setting: (Unbound)</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Set default politeness level to off: (Unbound)</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>
        Go to next/previous live region in the document's reading order:
        <keyseq><key>D</key></keyseq>/<keyseq><key>Shift</key><key>D</key></keyseq>
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Review the next/previous saved live region message: (Unbound)</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>
        Go to last live region which made an announcement:
        <keyseq><key>Y</key></keyseq>
      </p>
    </item>
</list>
